deck: Continuation of the Green Hornet series starring Britt Reid Jr.
description:
Begins at issue #34, continuing the original Green Hornet run starring Britt Reid Jr. as the Green Hornet.

The name change is most likely due to the release of another Green Hornet series starring the original Britt Reid as the Hornet.

Collected Editions

  • Green Hornet: Legacy (#34-42)
name: Green Hornet: Legacy

deck: Published March 2006 by Pen 2 Paper Entertainment.
description:
Published March 2006 as a single issue.

Charlie Stone, a mercenary mixed in magic, is recruited by the religious secret society, the Knights Templar. The Knights are the protectors of all holy objects. He is teamed up with a female partner named Jessie. Together they must infiltrate an evil group known as the Cross. The Cross believes it is their duty to speed the world along toward Armageddon.
name: The Descendants

description: Transformers Generations 2010 is a Japanese-exclusive book published by Million Publishing in 2010. The book covers Takara's 2010 anniversary line, the Takara and Hasbro releases of Animated, Hunt for the Decepticons toys, alongside concept sketches, design sketches, comics, and interviews with some of Takara's employees. It is a follow up to the Transformers Generations 2009.
name: Transformers Generations 2010

description: Transformers Generations 2012 is a Japanese-exclusive book published by Million Publishing in 2012. This book primarily showcases Transformers from the Japanese version of Prime toyline, Dark of the Moon toyline, as well as Transformers United and other Japanese exclusives. The books also have concept sketches, design sketches, comics, and interviews with some of Takara's employees. It follows Transformers Generations 2011.
name: Transformers Generations 2012
